http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Cancer-detection-camp-held/article13980094.ece

A cancer detection camp was organised by Lions Club of Krishnapuram at Kayamkulam recently. About 300 patients were examined by a panel of doctors from the Regional Cancer Centre, Thiruvananthapuram. The camp detected cancer in many persons. An abnormally high rate of incidence had been reported by doctors, the club said in a release. All the patients had begun treatment at the RCC, the statement said. Four more medical camps would be conducted in future, according to the organisers. â€” Special Correspondent